{"content_type":"tech","visual_kind":"workflow_map","title":"Memento Pattern","subtitle":"Undo by restoring snapshots, not by reversing operations","eyebrow":"Behavioral Pattern","panels":[{"heading":"Originator","tag":"Source","bullets":["Object whose state needs save/restore","Creates opaque Memento snapshot","Restores from Memento directly"]},{"heading":"Memento","tag":"Snapshot","bullets":["Immutable capture of state","Caretaker cannot read internals","Deep copy required for safety"]},{"heading":"Caretaker","tag":"History","bullets":["Holds stack/ring of Mementos","Manages undo depth limits","Does NOT understand snapshot contents"]},{"heading":"vs Command","tag":"Distinction","bullets":["Memento: undo = restore snapshot","Command: undo = run reverse operation","Choose by undo model complexity"]}],"footer":"Memento = snapshot undo. If reverse operations are simpler, use Command. Always manage memory with bounded history.","output_path":"assets/design-pattern/images/memento-overview.png"}
